api-1  | What excites you about a career in engineering/technology? Why do you think your abilities and skills are a good fit for
api-1  | Plaksha's B.Tech program?
api-1  | I always wanted to do engineering as i always loved experimenting with computer, mobile devices.The current trend is moving towards new
api-1  | technology and improvements to the existing hardware and software at a rapid pace.I as a student need to be ahead of my competition by
api-1  | choosing a good institute like plaksha which not only offers great teacher student ratio but also regular hackathons, labs and research
api-1  | facilities , students of plaksha winning the hackathon organised by yale is also a great achievement which i suppose would only be possible
api-1  | with the right guidance by faculty and also the efforts of students .I as a tech enthusiast would love being under the guidance of such
api-1  | esteemed faculty , i have already learnt basics of java and published a few games in google play store , thus possesing a good foundation
api-1  | which could be polished under the faculty of plaksha.The b.tech program at plaksha is going to be very useful for someone like me who is
api-1  | intrested in tech , plaksha has a huge number of clubs which would also be great for overall development,I personally like chess a lot and
api-1  | also have won a few state tournaments when i was younger, i would definitely love reviving that hobby of mine at plaksha which has a huge
api-1  | number of clubs and option for new clubs.Maths being my favourite subject and also my strongest with the exception of mechanics in physics
api-1  | as it requires visualisation would be very helpful in my competitive programs.The best part of technology is that it can go on forever meaning
api-1  | i would have the oportunity to learn forever and explore many of the untouched , yet to be discovered parts of it.Plaksha having a vast
api-1  | number of reaserch labs and other things to support students would support me learn new things about technology and other things that i
api-1  | would need to know about engineering.
api-1  | Share a time when you contributed to a project or activity that positively affected your school or community. What
api-1  | challenges did you face, and what did you learn about leadership and perseverance?
api-1  | I was almost always the head of the group when we were doing a science project / science fair.There were many times when the intitial idea
api-1  | was good but many improvements could have been made later on.One such incident was us designing a alarm for water tank the initial
api-1  | prototype had a basic wire with a metal strip at the bottom of the tank and then another at the top of it , the alarm would go off when the
api-1  | circuit was complete i.e water is completely filled, there were a few reasons why this prototype was good but not the best way.The first was
api-1  | the risk of corrosion at the metal plate especially the bottom one, we simply fixed that by moving both the metal strips to the top. another
api-1  | problem was this wasnt universal i.e didnot work for pure , distilled water which couldve been a limitation , we fixed this by having a closed
api-1  | enclosure with the bottom open and the insides having a earbud which had a thin lining of metal on top and a metal strip on top of the
api-1  | enclousure , the earbud being light and with less density would float up and hit the metal strip completing the circuit this eliminated the
api-1  | factor of conductance of water , this new setup now could be used in many places with a liquid system or even pressure chambers when
api-1  | build with enough resistance for the movement of earbud. outside of the setup was a simple 9v battery and a buzzer which would normally
api-1  | work and the setup acting as our switch. similar setup (initial prototype) was also used as a alarm mechanism for doors with an addition of a
api-1  | spring at the hinge which would make buzzer go off even at slight opening of door and also let the door be completely open, the metal strips
api-1  | are attached at the hinge and wall , the strip on the wall had spring to complete circuit at the slightest opening.We used a switch in the
api-1  | second system as we didnt want it to ring when we our clasroom doors were open while teaching.
